	<a class="visually-hidden skip-to-text-link focusable" href="#start-of-content">Skip Article Header. Skip to: Start of Article.</a>

	<header id="post-header" class='standard mob-marg-t-med mob-marg-b-25 med-marg-b-50 big-marg-b-50 marg-t-50 clearfix' data-js='postHeader'>

		<ul tabindex="0" role='list' aria-label="Metadata for article." class="center metadata marg-b-sm mob-marg-b-sm">

		<li tabindex="0" class="byline marg-r-sm inline-block mob-marg-b-sm">
		<span class='visually-hidden'>Author: ChrisKohler.</span>
		<span class="link-underline-sm marg-r-sm" itemprop="author">
			<a tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true" role="presentation" rel="author" href="https://www.wired.com/author/chriskohler/">ChrisKohler</a>		</span>
		<span tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true" role="presentation" itemprop="articleSection">
			Culture		</span>
	</li>
	<li tabindex="0" class="meta-pubdate marg-r-sm inline-block">
		<span class='visually-hidden'>Date of Publication: 12.19.12.</span>
		<time aria-hidden="true" role="presentation" pubdate="December 19, 2012">12.19.12</time>
	</li>
	<li tabindex="0" class='marg-r-sm inline-block'>
		<span class='visually-hidden'>Time of Publication: 9:30 am.</span>
		<time aria-hidden="true" role="presentation" >9:30 am</time>
	</li>
	<meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2012-12-19T09:30:18+00:00"/>
	<meta itemprop="image"  content="https://www.wired.com/wp-content/uploads/images_blogs/gamelife/2012/12/lebling_blank650-200x100.jpg" />
		</ul>

		<h1 tabindex="0" class="post-title mob-marg-b-25 med-marg-b-50 big-marg-b-50" itemprop="name" data-js="postTitle">Text Adventure: <cite>Zork</cite> Creators Honored With Pioneer Award</h1>
		<figure id="attachment_52954" class="wp-caption  alignnone  relative" data-js=""><div class="ui-social-wrapper image absolute top right">
							<ul class="no-marg"><li><a class="fb clearfix no-underline no-outline" onclick="window.open( 'https://www.facebook.com/dialog/feed?display=popup&app_id=719405864858490&link=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2F2012%2F12%2Fzork-infocom-pioneer-award%2F&picture=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2Fimages_blogs%2Fgamelife%2F2012%2F12%2Flebling_blank660.jpg&redirect_uri=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2F2012%2F12%2Fzork-infocom-pioneer-award%2F' , 'Facebook' , 'height=580, width=730' )"><i aria-hidden="true" role="presentation" class="ui ui-social-xtra-sm ui-fb-xtra-sm active bg-fb"></i></a></li><li><a  class="pint clearfix no-underline no-outline" onclick="window.open( 'https://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wired.com%2F2012%2F12%2Fzork-infocom-pioneer-award%2F&is_video=true&media=https://www.wired.com/wp-content/uploads/images_blogs/gamelife/2012/12/lebling_blank660.jpg&description=Text%20Adventure%3A%20%3Ccite%3EZork%3C%2Fcite%3E%20Creators%20Honored%20With%20Pioneer%20Award%20%7C%20%20Infocom%20co-founders%20Dave%20Lebling%20%28left%29%20and%20Marc%20Blank%20%28right%29%2C%20pictured%20here%20in%201985%20with%20former%20Infocom%20employee%20Pat%20Maroni%2C%20will%20be%20honored%20with%20the%20AIAS%20Pioneer%20Award%20in%20February.%20%20%7C%20Credit%3APhoto%20courtesy%20Dave%20Lebling%20%7C%20From%20WIRED.com' , 'Pinterest' , 'height=580, width=730' )"><i aria-hidden="true" role="presentation" data-js="social"  class="ui ui-social-xtra-sm ui-pint-xtra-sm active bg-pint"></i></a></li></ul>
							</div><img class="size-full wp-image-52954" srcset="https://assets.wired.com/photos/w_280/wp-content/uploads/images_blogs/gamelife/2012/12/lebling_blank660.jpg 280w, https://assets.wired.com/photos/w_335/wp-content/uploads/images_blogs/gamelife/2012/12/lebling_blank660.jpg 335w, https://assets.wired.com/photos/w_560/wp-content/uploads/images_blogs/gamelife/2012/12/lebling_blank660.jpg 560w, https://assets.wired.com/photos/w_582/wp-content/uploads/images_blogs/gamelife/2012/12/lebling_blank660.jpg 582w, https://assets.wired.com/photos/w_660/wp-content/uploads/images_blogs/gamelife/2012/12/lebling_blank660.jpg 660w" sizes="(min-width: 1133px) 582px, (min-width: 961px) and (max-width: 1132px) 730px, (min-width: 768px) and (max-width: 960px) calc(100vw - (50px * 2)), (max-width: 767px) calc(100vw - (20px * 2)), 730px" data-pin-description="Text Adventure: Zork Creators Honored With Pioneer Award" src="https://assets.wired.com/photos/w_660/wp-content/uploads/images_blogs/gamelife/2012/12/lebling_blank660.jpg" /><figcaption class="wp-caption-text link-underline"><!--Generated in 1.616 ms--></a> Infocom co-founders Dave Lebling (left) and Marc Blank (right), pictured here in 1985 with former Infocom employee Pat Maroni, will be honored with the AIAS Pioneer Award in February. <em>Photo courtesy Dave Lebling</em></figcaption></figure>	</header>

	<section tabindex="0" class='post-container clearfix relative' data-js='post' id="start-of-content">
		<article class='content link-underline relative body-copy' data-js='content' itemprop="articleBody">

			<p>In the days before graphics, computer games had to entice players with nothing more than a well-turned phrase.</p>
<p>Whether you prefer to call them &#8220;text adventures&#8221; or &#8220;interactive fiction,&#8221; games played with nothing but writing and verbal commands were a significant part of the early days of interactive entertainment. At the forefront of the medium were the designers of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infocom">Infocom</a>, which created and published text games like <cite>Zork</cite>, <cite>Starcross</cite> and <cite>The Hitchhiker&#8217;s Guide to the Galaxy</cite> that delighted players with clever writing and had them absolutely tearing their hair out with difficult puzzles.</p>
<p>Today, Wired can exclusively report that Marc Blank and Dave Lebling, two of the co-founders of Infocom and co-creators of <cite>Zork</cite>, will be honored with the Academy of Interactive Arts and Sciences&#8217; Pioneer Award at the <a href="http://www.dicesummit.org/">DICE Summit</a> in February. The award is given to the gamemakers whose groundbreaking early work laid the foundations of the multi-billion-dollar videogame industry. Previous recipients include <a href="https://www.wired.com/gamelife/2010/01/david-crane-pioneer/">David Crane, creator of <cite>Pitfall!</cite></a>, and <a href="https://www.wired.com/gamelife/2011/11/ed-logg-pioneer-award/"><em>Asteroids</em> designer Ed Logg</a>.</p>
<p>Wired spoke to Dave Lebling, as well as another Infocom designer, for this story. But in honor of their achievements and their medium of choice, we&#8217;ve decided to present the results of our interviews in a text adventure of our own, below. You&#8217;ll have to play to find out more.</p>
<p><iframe id="embed" frameborder="1" width="660px" height="700px" src="https://playfic.com/parchment/?game=/releases/c/c55a95a7-8497-4208-93cd-5b5e517f02a9/c55a95a7-8497-4208-93cd-5b5e517f02a9.z8"></iframe></p>
<p><em>Thanks to <a href="http://playfic.com">Playfic</a> for the text adventure tech!</em></p>

			<a class="visually-hidden skip-to-text-link focusable bg-white" href="#start-of-content">Go Back to Top. Skip To: Start of Article.</a>

			
